{
  "stem": "13395.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So she went, took a few things together, her parents' photos, in a little suitcase that my father had from 1920-- 1914.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she went to Sosnowiec, to the same holding camp, to the [NON-ENGLISH], where I was held, asked the guard to let her in, and walked down straight to the office of the commander, and said, I would like you-- I came here on my own will, and I would ask you to send me to be with my children.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They are in concentration camp in Ober Altstadt in Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He says, just a moment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When was it?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She said, about a year ago.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Oh, he says, I remember.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He took a Nazi guard, an SS guard, put her on a train, and sent her to Ober Altstadt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We, of course, not knowing anything where our parents are, thought that all, that they were all deported, because these rumors came back, because the young people were sent to work, and the old people were, went right to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we knew what happened to the ghettos, not knowing was our parents with the young or the old.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were getting ready to go to camp on a Saturday afternoon after work, when we were all lined up-- and we were always being counted, always being counted-- and I see on the bridge across, an SS guard with a woman with a little suitcase.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as they came closer, I cried out to my sister, Hannah, this is our mother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was the last time I called her mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was the only mother in camp, and I could not put-- how many were we then?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About 800 by then.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The camp grew to 800.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
